text: Jemaluang (Chinese: 三板头 / 任罗宏) is a town and mukim in Mersing District, Johor, Malaysia.http://www.utusan.com.my/berita/nahas-bencana/kakitangan-saj-mersing- parah-anak-maut-1.87556 ==Geography== Jemaluang in Mersing District Jemaluang lies on the intersection of national highway 3 and 50. The mukim (commune) surrounding the town spans over an area of 124 km2 and also includes 10 nearby villages.http://www.mdmersing.gov.my/ms/pelawat/info-mersing/keluasan-daerah ==Geology== The mukim also includes Belunak Island.http://www.mdmersing.gov.my/ms/pelawat/info-mersing/senarai-nama-mukim It is worth noting that Jemaluang is not located in mukim Jemaluang. ==References== Category:Mukims of Johor
title: Jemaluang
